  "title": "Site Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p><br>\nThe role requires hands-on management of site works, ensuring proper coordination, quality, and timely delivery of ACMV installations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>· Manage and supervise daily ACMV site activities, including installation, testing, and commissioning.</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with subcontractors, consultants, and internal teams to ensure smooth execution of works.</p>\n<p>· Monitor project schedules, manpower allocation, and material delivery to meet milestones.</p>\n<p>· Ensure compliance with design specifications, quality standards, and workplace safety regulations.</p>\n<p>· Resolve site-related technical and coordination issues promptly.</p>\n<p>· Conduct regular site inspections and prepare progress reports for management.</p>\n<p>· Provide guidance and support to site engineers, supervisors, and workers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· Diploma/Degree in Mechanical Engineering, Building Services, or related discipline.</p>\n<p>· Minimum 5–8 years of ACMV site management experience in large-scale construction projects.</p>\n<p>· Strong knowledge of ACMV systems installation, testing, and commissioning.</p>\n<p>· Good understanding of local codes, standards, and safety regulations.</p>\n<p>· Proven ability to manage subcontractors and coordinate across multiple stakeholders.</p>\n<p>· Strong leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills.</p>\n<p>· Able to work on-site full time at Tuas.</p>\n<p>· Willingness to work at Tuas area. Transportation is provided from nearest MRT station to site office</p>",
